Similarly, this example uses `Tendsto.comp`. We have `a` tends to `𝓝 (-1)` along `atTop` (ha) and `φ` tends to `𝓝 (Complex.I)` along `𝓝 (-1)` (hφ). Applying `Tendsto.comp` with these two facts yields that `φ ∘ a` tends to `𝓝 (Complex.I)` along `atTop`.

These examples are direct applications of the `Tendsto.comp` lemma, which itself is a consequence of the continuity of functions with respect to filters.

